3
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:15,400
In this video we’re going to talk about
the American vowel sound /ə/,

4
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:18,880
as in the word “ago”.

5
00:00:19,620 --> 00:00:22,220
You can also hear this sound in words like

6
00:00:22,240 --> 00:00:23,040
“above,”

7
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:24,380
“person,”

8
00:00:24,580 --> 00:00:25,680
“parent,”

9
00:00:25,740 --> 00:00:27,280
or “action”.

10
00:00:28,080 --> 00:00:33,840
Please, note that we’ll be using a special phonetic symbol - /ə/ - for this sound.

11
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:41,480
The /ə/ sound is one of the two most frequently used vowel sounds in American English.

12
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:47,300
In fact, one in every five words has the /ə/ sound.

13
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:51,360
If you want to pronounce it like an American, keep watching.

14
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:54,020
OK.

15
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:59,760
To pronounce the /ə/ sound, you should focus on relaxing your tongue and lips.

16
00:01:00,780 --> 00:01:08,220
Slightly open your mouth, relax your lips, and leave them in a neutral position.

17
00:01:10,340 --> 00:01:15,020
Place your tongue in the middle of your mouth and relax it.

18
00:01:22,420 --> 00:01:30,040
Remember, the /ə/ sound is very relaxed, so your tongue and lips should be relaxed when you pronounce it.

19
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:34,120
